Deputy president William Ruto's goose seems to have been cooked last year when the powerful national management committee was reconstituted with DP's allies being ejected. And slowly, Ruto's hold onto the party's key organs was systematically replaced giving president Uhuru Kenyatta the muscles to solely run the party. Our senior reporter Patrick Amimo gives us the perspective of how the DP Ruto has lost big in the ruling party.&nbsp;